# Attestack evidence

This project uses [Attestack](https://kiket-dev.github.io/attestack/) for tamper-evident session records.

## Before substantive work

Confirm an Attestack session is open. If not, tell the user to run:

```bash
attestack start "short task title"
```

## During work

Use Attestack MCP tools when available:

- `attestack_status` — check the active session
- `attestack_note` — record milestones or review notes
- `attestack_agent_tool_call` — record significant tool use (hashes preferred over raw content)
- `attestack_agent_decision` — record important decisions
- `attestack_snapshot` — capture Git state after meaningful changes

Run tests and builds through the shell with Attestack when possible:

```bash
attestack run -- npm test
```

## Privacy

Do not store raw prompts or secrets in notes. Use content hashes for sensitive material.

## When finished

Remind the user:

```bash
attestack stop
attestack bundle create
```
